    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Elemental Disciplines\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"3\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p80\">Elemental Disciplines</span></h3><p>The elemental disciplines are presented in alphabetical order. If a discipline requires a level, you must be the level in this class to learn the discipline.</p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p></p><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Breath of Winter (17th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Breath of Winter (17th Level Required).</span> You can spend 6 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.9eANbJeKnbPCPRHs].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Clench of the North Wind (6th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Clench of the North Wind (6th Level Required).</span> You can spend 3 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.XcrEHiBrF54Bcnjd].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Elemental Attunement\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Elemental Attunement.</span> You can use your action to briefly control elemental forces within 30 feet of you, causing one of the following effects of your choice:</p><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">Create a harmless, instantaneous sensory effect related to air, earth, fire, or water, such as a shower of sparks, a puff of wind, a spray of light mist, or a gentle rumbling of stone.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Instantaneously light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Chill or warm up to 1 pound of nonliving material for up to 1 hour.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Cause earth, fire, water, or mist that can fit within a 1-foot cube to shape itself into a crude form you designate for 1 minute.</li></ul></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Eternal Mountain Defense (17th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Eternal Mountain Defense (17th Level Required).</span> You can spend 5 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.5FDreatLWrKMlwrx], targeting yourself.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Fangs of the Fire Snake\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Fangs of the Fire Snake.</span> When you use the @action[Attack] action on your turn, you can spend 1 ki point to cause tendrils of flame to stretch out from your fists and feet. Your reach with your unarmed strikes increases by 10 feet for that action, as well as the rest of the turn. A hit with such an attack deals fire damage instead of bludgeoning damage, and if you spend 1 ki point when the attack hits, it also deals an extra [[/damage 1d10 type=fire]] damage.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Fist of Four Thunders\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Fist of Four Thunders.</span> You can spend 2 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.eblKmCn9x7A9n3IM].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Flames of the Phoenix (11th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Flames of the Phoenix (11th Level Required).</span> You can spend 4 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.uGu9D0QJtYH33DrE].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Gong of the Summit (6th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Gong of the Summit (6th Level Required).</span> You can spend 3 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.sFwnTTVcEb0dY5By].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Mist Stance (11th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Mist Stance (11th Level Required).</span> You can spend 4 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.pKSVW0LQRKIxMIuY], targeting yourself.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Ride the Wind (11th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Ride the Wind (11th Level Required).</span> You can spend 4 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.UCpMgIrTiipKBrwl], targeting yourself.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"River of Hungry Flame (17th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">River of Hungry Flame (17th Level Required).</span> You can spend 5 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.VLVLp92QAZm5LMZF].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Rush of the Gale Spirits\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Rush of the Gale Spirits.</span> You can spend 2 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.4mwMeYMmmaGE9nqk].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Shape the Flowing River\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Shape the Flowing River.</span> As an action, you can spend 1 ki point to choose an area of ice or water no larger than 30 feet on a side within 120 feet of you. You can change water to ice within the area and vice versa, and you can reshape ice in the area in any manner you choose. You can raise or lower the ice's elevation, create or fill in a trench, erect or flatten a wall, or form a pillar. The extent of any such changes can't exceed half the area's largest dimension. For example, if you affect a 30-foot square, you can create a pillar up to 15 feet high. raise or lower the square's elevation by up to 15 feet, dig a trench up to 15 feet deep, and so on. You can't shape the ice to trap or injure a creature in the area.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Sweeping Cinder Strike\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Sweeping Cinder Strike.</span> You can spend 2 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.WGdHm2U73KdKbVJ2].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Unbroken Air\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Unbroken Air.</span> You can create a blast of compressed air that strikes like a mighty fist. As an action, you can spend 2 ki points and choose a creature within 30 feet of you. That creature must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/damage 3d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage, plus an extra [[/damage 1d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage for each additional ki point you spend, and you can push the creature up to 20 feet away from you and knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone]. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and you don't push it or knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Water Whip\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Water Whip.</span> You can spend 2 ki points as an action to create a whip of water that shoves and pulls a creature to unbalance it. A creature that you can see that is within 30 feet of you must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/damage 3d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage, plus an extra [[/damage 1d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage for each additional ki point you spend, and you can either knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone] or pull it up to 25 feet closer to you. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and you don't pull it or knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone].</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Wave of Rolling Earth (17th Level Required)\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Player’s Handbook (2014), p81\">Wave of Rolling Earth (17th Level Required).</span> You can spend 6 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.iLfkkZ2PipZIbR8b].</p></div></div></div></div>",
